title: Warburg coefficient
summary: The Warburg coefficient (or Warburg constant; denoted AW or σ) is the diffusion coefficient of ions in solution, associated to the Warburg element, ZW.  The Warburg coefficient has units of Ω / seconds = Ω ( s − 1 / 2 ) {\displaystyle {\Omega }/{\sqrt {\text{seconds}}}={\Omega }(s^{-1/2})}
